{"questionId":"3019258","questionHtml":"<p>use the result from part (e)(ii) to show that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mo>)</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempts to equate two expressions for either <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow><mi>a</mi></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempts to use <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi></math> with <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi></math></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mo>)</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>d</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempts to use <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>d</mi></math>&nbsp;with <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>b</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>b</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>b</mi></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>b</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>b</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(A1)M1</strong></em> for any valid approach that correctly leads to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> (or equivalent).<br>Do not accept numerical verification from the <em><strong>AG</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>so <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>)</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>d</mi></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mo>)</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>d</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempts to equate two expressions for either <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><msub><mi>r</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>d</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>d</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; <strong>OR&nbsp;</strong> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>(</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>d</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>d</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mi>a</mi></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>a</mi><mi>d</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>d</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Do not accept numerical verification from the <em><strong>AG</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>so <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em>&nbsp;</p>","meta":{"questionId":"3019258","referenceCode":"23M.3.AHL.TZ2.2eiii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"use the result from part (e)(ii) to show that b=0 or a=-12.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"iii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.3—Geometric sequences and series","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.6—Simple proof"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}